# Git sync — Mac (agent) ↔ GitHub ↔ Windows (testing)

This repo is edited on **macOS** (agent) and tested on **Windows** (operator). GitHub is the handoff. `git pull` on Windows only works after the agent **pushes**.

**Default branch for active work:** `feature/sprint-1-m1` (check `git branch` if unsure).

---

## Agent — when to commit and push

### MUST commit + push (same session, no need to ask)

- Any change under `src/EventPlatform.PrintRelay.App/` or `src/EventPlatform.PrintRelay.Spike/` the user will run on Windows
- Bug fixes reported from Windows testing
- User says **commit**, **push**, or **commit and push**
- Story work marked Done that includes runnable app behaviour

Use one commit per logical fix/feature. Message: what/why (not a file list).

### MUST NOT commit or push unless the user asks

- Read-only answers, plans, or investigations with **no code changes**
- User says **don't commit** or **don't push**
- Partial/WIP that does not meet story acceptance (unless user explicitly wants a WIP push)

### After every push — tell the user in the reply

1. **Branch:** e.g. `feature/sprint-1-m1`
2. **Commit:** short SHA + subject line, e.g. `cb22916 Fix tray startup deadlock…`
3. **Reminder:** run the Windows sync steps below before `dotnet publish`

Core-only / tests / docs-only changes: push is optional; say **“Not pushed — Windows exe unchanged”** or push if bundled with App changes in the same session.

---

## Operator — sync Windows before every test

Run in **PowerShell** on the Windows PC (`C:\Users\Deon\event-platform-print-relay-windows` or your clone path).

### 1. Pull latest (required after agent says it pushed)

```powershell
cd C:\Users\Deon\event-platform-print-relay-windows
git fetch origin
git checkout feature/sprint-1-m1
git pull origin feature/sprint-1-m1
git log -1 --oneline
```

**Check:** `git log -1` matches the commit SHA/subject the agent gave you. If not, you are not on the right branch or pull failed.

### 2. Stop the old app (required before publish)

```powershell
taskkill /IM EventPlatform.PrintRelay.exe /F
```

### 3. Publish

```powershell
dotnet publish src\EventPlatform.PrintRelay.App -c Release -r win-x64 --self-contained -o artifacts\app
```

Publish must end with `-> ...\artifacts\app\` and **no** `MSB3027` file-lock errors.

### 4. Verify build (safe — no dialog)

```powershell
.\artifacts\app\EventPlatform.PrintRelay.exe --version
(Get-Item .\artifacts\app\EventPlatform.PrintRelay.exe).VersionInfo.FileVersion
Get-Content .\artifacts\app\build-info.txt
```

Use **`--version`** (console text). Avoid **`--about`** unless troubleshooting UI.

### 5. Run

```powershell
.\artifacts\app\EventPlatform.PrintRelay.exe
```

Tray icon may be under the **^** overflow by the clock.

---

## If Windows says “Already up to date” but behaviour is old

- Confirm branch: `git branch --show-current` → must match agent’s branch
- Confirm remote: `git log -1 --oneline` vs agent’s SHA
- Agent may not have pushed yet — ask for push or check GitHub
